<div class="modal">
  <input id="mining-modal" type="checkbox" />
  <label for="mining-modal" class="overlay"></label>
  <article>
    <header>
      <h3>What the heck is "mining"?</h3>
      <label for="mining-modal" class="close">&times;</label>
    </header>
    <section class="content">
      <p>
        Cryptocurrencies are digital currencies (Bitcoin is one of them) with no
        central government behind them. Because of this, there's no central mint
        either—instead, coins are created by a process called
        <strong>mining</strong>.
      </p>
      <p class="top-margin-tiny">
        Computers mine by doing little bits of math that help to process
        transactions. This keeps the currency usable! In exchange for doing this
        work, the computers are rewarded with a small amount of new currency,
        adding new coins to the system. It's one big happy cycle!
      </p>
    </section>
    <footer>
      <label for="mining-modal" class="button modal-button">
        Got it!
      </label>
    </footer>
  </article>
</div>
